ort%22%7D%5D" btn_text="Buy Now" btn_link="#0" open_link="true"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width="stretch_row_content" equal_height="yes" content_placement="middle" overlay_dotted="" css=".vc_custom_1544527280599{background-color: #1c1f26 !important;}"][vc_column css=".vc_custom_1534156862831{padding-top: 0px !important;padding-right: 0px !important;padding-left: 0px !important;}" offset="vc_col-lg-6 vc_col-md-12 vc_col-xs-12"][vc_single_image img_size="full" css=".vc_custom_1545040506033{margin-bottom: 0px !important;}"][/vc_column][vc_column css=".vc_custom_1534156868484{padding-top: 3px !important;background-color: #1c1f26 !important;}" offset="vc_col-lg-6 vc_col-md-12 vc_col-xs-12"][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width="1/2" css=".vc_custom_1533967073524{padding-right: 5% !important;padding-left: 15% !important;}"][hanor_services stunnhing_services="" open_link="true" image_icon="icon-tab" service_icon="pe-7s-shuffle" service_title="url:%230|title:Marketing%20Strategy||" title_color="#ffffff" content_color="#ffffff" service_btm="0px" service_item_btm="0px"]SEO is most important part to run a successful business. Organic searches only stays as lifetime.[/hanor_services][hanor_services stunnhing_services="" open_link="true" image_icon="icon-tab" service_icon="pe-7s-edit" service_title="url:%230|title:Digital%20Marketing||" title_color="#ffffff" content_color="#ffffff" service_top="0px" service_item_top="0px"]We constantly hear your feedbacks that you get better a experience while you’re using our WordPress themes.[/hanor_services][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width="1/2" css=".vc_custom_1533967078955{padding-right: 15% !important;padding-left: 5% !important;}"][hanor_services stunnhing_services="" open_link="true" image_icon="icon-tab" service_icon="pe-7s-target" service_title="url:%230|title:Brand%20Development||" title_color="#ffffff" content_color="#ffffff" service_btm="0px" service_item_btm="0px"]Having these multiple page designs, The site will adapt &amp; comfortably work in any type of device regarding to it’s size.[/hanor_services][hanor_services stunnhing_services="" open_link="true" image_icon="icon-tab" service_icon="pe-7s-exapnd2" service_title="url:%230|title:Growth%20%26%20Innovation||" title_color="#ffffff" content_color="#ffffff" service_top="0px" service_item_top="0px"]Take your business further with flexible credit and reward programs, and floorplan and leasing options.[/hanor_services][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width="stretch_row" overlay_dotted="" css=".vc_custom_1544003683890{padding-top: 7% !important;background-color: #f9f9f9 !important;}"][vc_column][havnor_section_title title_text="General Questions" content_text="Find a short list of our most frequently asked questions." btm_space="5%"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width="stretch_row" overlay_dotted="" css=".vc_custom_1544003733838{padding-bottom: 7% !important;background-color: #f9f9f9 !important;}"][vc_column css=".vc_custom_1530614708280{padding-top: 0px !important;}" offset="vc_col-lg-6 vc_col-md-12"][vc_accordion one_active="true" active_tab="2"][vc_accordion_tab title="What industries do you specialize in?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1540448007841{margin-top: 0px !important;margin-bottom: 0px !important;padding-top: 0px !important;padding-bottom: 0px !important;}"]We take pride in our ability to learn the fundamentals of virtually any industry or technology quickly. Some of the markets we have served include green technologies, medical devices, biotechnology, Internet/e-commerce, telecommunications, distance education/e-learning, real estate, financial services, healthcare services, manufacturing, retail, food service, consumer products, media and entertainment, aerospace, artificial intelligence, enterprise software, insurance, energy, and networking. Having said that, we believe that the value we bring to the table is not industry expertise — which you already possess in abundance — but rather an understanding of what investors like to see in a potential opportunity.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="Can you guarantee that our plan will raise capital?" sub_title="Sub Title 2"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1540448048249{margin-top: 0px !important;margin-bottom: 0px !important;padding-top: 0px !important;padding-bottom: 0px !important;}"]Of course not. Nobody can make that guarantee (and if somebody ever makes that guarantee, it’s a good idea to run away quickly). A good plan is essential, but a plan alone will not get funded. Although we will do our best to help you prepare, we have no control over how well you present yourselves to investors, or how well you answer their questions. We can coach and we can mentor, but at the end of the day, it’s your business and you must close the deal.
[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="Can you help us raise money?"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1540448085794{margin-top: 0px !important;margin-bottom: 0px !important;padding-top: 0px !important;padding-bottom: 0px !important;}"]We can sometimes make informal introductions to potential investors or other intermediaries. In general, only brokers licensed with the Financial Industry Regulatory Authority (FINRA) can legally arrange financing (see Beware of Finders in our Blog). Please seek legal counsel and make sure that any “finder” you talk to is properly licensed with FINRA before you hire them. Failing to do so may expose you and your company to significant liability.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="Do we really need a business plan?"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1540448126120{margin-top: 0px !important;margin-bottom: 0px !important;padding-top: 0px !important;padding-bottom: 0px !important;}"]If you run a business, then it’s probably safe to say yes. In fact, you may require more than one business plan: one for raising capital and one for running your business. The former is a compact, easily digested strategic document that is designed to persuade potential investors to pick up the phone and invite you to their offices for an initial meeting. The latter is a more detailed document serving as a day-to-day roadmap, detailing the tactics supporting your overall strategy. The former needs to be an attractive document that sells; the latter can be a collection of spreadsheets, lists, research summaries, and other documents stuffed in a binder that you refer to and update on a regular basis. We specialize in preparing the capital-raising business plan, but many of the by-products are suitable for use in the operating business plan.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="Why should hire a consultant to our business plan?"][vc_column_text]You could easily spend 500 hours or more preparing an investor-grade business plan, financial forecast, and investor presentation, even if you have an MBA. This is time you should probably be spending building your team, product, distribution channels, and customer base. In addition to our expertise in preparing these materials, we offer independent, third-party insights into your business, and may raise questions that you might not have thought to ask.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][/vc_accordion][/vc_column][vc_column css=".vc_custom_1530614727224{padding-top: 0px !important;}" offset="vc_col-lg-6 vc_col-md-12"][vc_accordion one_active="true" active_tab="5"][vc_accordion_tab title="What makes your business plans so special?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1540448186218{margin-top: 0px !important;margin-bottom: 0px !important;padding-top: 0px !important;padding-bottom: 0px !important;}"]Most importantly, they work. In a world in which fewer than 1 in 250 business plans ever raise venture capital, we are happy to report that about half of our plans have raised capital, and a good portion of the rest resulted in an acquisition or currently have commitments for investment from prior round investors. Each plan is handcrafted to reflect the client’s specific circumstances, yet share attributes that investors find appealing.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="What makes your financial projections special?" sub_title="Sub Title 2"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1540448209678{margin-top: 0px !important;margin-bottom: 0px !important;padding-top: 0px !important;padding-bottom: 0px !important;}"]Balance sheets that balance. Cash flows, income statements, and balance sheets that tie together (you’d be surprised by how many consultants who don’t get the basics right). Fully assumption-driven, so that you can do what-if analyses. Depending on your needs, we can include a lot of very sophisticated features – learn more about our financial projections here.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="How long does it take?"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1540448237565{margin-top: 0px !important;margin-bottom: 0px !important;padding-top: 0px !important;padding-bottom: 0px !important;}"]For a typical engagement, consisting of a business plan, financial forecast, and investor presentation, the typical time to completion is 6-8 weeks, as illustrated below. The actual time can be influenced by the quality of your existing materials, the level of your participation, the complexity of your market and business model, and our current workload.

[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="Can you work any faster?"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1540448262790{margin-top: 0px !important;margin-bottom: 0px !important;padding-top: 0px !important;padding-bottom: 0px !important;}"]Yes, but we may need to charge a “rush” fee. We typically work on multiple projects at any point in time, and rush projects can strain our schedules or inconvenience other clients.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="What is your refund policy?"][vc_column_text]Your initial payment is non-refundable. This is because by the time you have decided to hire us, we have already set aside time to work with you, and we may even have turned away other opportunities in order to provide you with the best possible experience. Subsequent payments are subject to a pro-rated refund if you choose to terminate the project before we have fully earned the subsequent payment. For example, suppose fees for your project are broken into three payments, each covering 20 hours of services. [/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][/vc_accordion][/vc_column][/vc_row]
CONTENT;
